  "explanation": "While both the source (.NET EF Core) and target (Java Spring Data MongoDB) validations passed individually, the DeepDiff equivalence check failed with a fatal structural error: 'No matching query keys found between source and target.' This indicates that the translated queries do not semantically correspond to the originals in a way that can be automatically verified. Additionally, inspection of the executed queries reveals several logical mismatches: (1) Query 3 in the target limits the grouped result to a single document ($limit: 1) with secondary sorts that override the count-based ordering, whereas the source returns the full aggregation ordered by count; (2) Query 4 in the source computes a bounded TOP(50) subset and then extracts min/max quantities from it, while the target performs an unbounded find with no limit and no equivalent window logic; (3) Query 2 in the source joins multiple normalized tables including CustomerTransactions, but the target document model (as shown in entity validation) embeds only Customer and OrderLines, omitting CustomerTransactions and altering the relational join behavior. These discrepancies mean the translation is not logically equivalent and must be retried."  
